Construct a program in JAVA language that will input that a character (“I”, “N”, or “F”). 
Do the following output respect to the input.
Character "I", "N", "F" / I - GoodMorning, N- Goodafternoon, F- Goodevening.


import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
		
		System.out.print("CHOOSE WITHIN I,N,F: ");
		char letter = sc.next().charAt(0);
		
		
		
		if (letter == 'I') {
		    System.out.print("Good Morning");
		}
		
		else if (letter == 'N') {
		    System.out.print("Good Afternoon");
		}
		
		else if (letter == 'F') {
		    System.out.print("Good Evening");
		}
		
		else {
		    System.out.print("Invalid");
		}
		
		sc.close();
	}
}	
		
		
